# shift4_end.dtl
# End of Shift 4 - Fellow officer Murphy breaks down, Sasha shares more intel
# Builds emotional connection and advances conspiracy

audio music "res://assets/music/narrative/horror_fog_main.mp3" [fade="2.0" volume="-5.0" bus="Music"]
audio "res://assets/music/narrative/creepy_creaks_ambience.mp3" [volume="-12.0" bus="Ambient"]
[background arg="res://assets/narrative/checkpoint_corridor.png" fade="0.0"]

# Murphy's emotional breakdown scene - enhanced with deeper emotional impact
audio "res://assets/audio/footsteps/Concrete Walk 1_1.wav" [volume="-8.0" bus="SFX"]
join fellow_officer [z_index="1"]
fellow_officer: Murphy catches you in the corridor, eyes red-rimmed. Got a minute? #id:215

[background arg="res://assets/narrative/storage_room.png" fade="1.5"]
audio "res://assets/audio/furniture/Door Open C.wav" [volume="-8.0" bus="SFX"]
fellow_officer: Murphy pulls you into an empty storage room and closes the door. #id:216
fellow_officer: That joke I made in the cafeteria... about my cousin being in the [color=DARK_VIOLET]Root Reserve[/color] batch... #id:217
audio "res://assets/audio/stings/dread_chord.mp3" [volume="-8.0" bus="SFX"]
fellow_officer: Murphy's voice cracks. I don't think it was a joke anymore. #id:218

if {cafeteria_response} == "serious":
	fellow_officer: You said it wasn't funny. You were right. [color=STEEL_BLUE]Nothing about this is funny.[/color] #id:219
else:
	fellow_officer: I saw you leave. Smart. I wish I could stop eating that stuff, but they [color=YELLOW]watch[/color]. They always watch. #id:21a

fellow_officer: I found something in my cousin's belongings. His rejection form. Standard stuff, but... #id:21b
audio "res://assets/audio/paper/paper handled 1.wav" [volume="-5.0" bus="SFX"]
fellow_officer: Murphy pulls out a crumpled form. Look at the processing code. "[color=CRIMSON]RR-UTIL-7[/color]." #id:21c
fellow_officer: I looked it up in the archives. RR stands for [pulse freq=2][color=DARK_VIOLET]Root Reserve[/color][/pulse]. UTIL means... [color=CRIMSON]utilization[/color]. #id:21d

# Murphy's emotional breakdown
audio "res://assets/audio/stings/emotional_sting.mp3" [volume="-8.0" bus="SFX"]
fellow_officer: [wave amp=20 freq=3]Murphy's hands start shaking.[/wave] My cousin... Tommy... he was just twenty-three. #id:21d_breakdown1
fellow_officer: He came here for a [color=CHARTREUSE]better life[/color]. Failed one inspection. One. [color=STEEL_BLUE]Just bad timing.[/color] #id:21d_breakdown2
fellow_officer: Murphy slides down the wall, face in his hands. And I... I [tornado radius=3 freq=2][color=CRIMSON]ATE[/color][/tornado] that stuff. Every day. #id:21d_breakdown3
audio "res://assets/audio/stings/dread_chord.mp3" [volume="-5.0" bus="SFX"]
fellow_officer: Murphy looks up at you, tears streaming. [pulse freq=2][color=CRIMSON]What if I ate HIM?[/color][/pulse] #id:21d_breakdown4

set {murphy_alliance} = "none"
- "Murphy... I'm so sorry. I'm with you. We'll find the truth together." #id:21e
	set {murphy_alliance} = "ally"
- "Murphy, this is dangerous. We should stay out of it." #id:21f
	set {murphy_alliance} = "cautious"
- "Maybe it's a coincidence. Let's not jump to conclusions." #id:220
	set {murphy_alliance} = "skeptical"

if {murphy_alliance} == "ally":
	join fellow_officer [z_index="1"]
	join player_character [z_index="1"]
	player_character: You kneel beside Murphy, putting a hand on his shoulder. #id:221_comfort1
	leave player_character
	fellow_officer: Murphy grabs your arm like a lifeline. [color=CHARTREUSE]Thank you.[/color] I thought I was going crazy. #id:221
	fellow_officer: [color=STEEL_BLUE]His voice steadies slightly.[/color] For Tommy. We do this for Tommy. And everyone else they've taken. #id:221_tommy
	fellow_officer: There's others who suspect too. Sasha's been gathering people. I think she trusts you. #id:222
	leave fellow_officer
elif {murphy_alliance} == "cautious":
	join fellow_officer [z_index="1"]
	fellow_officer: Murphy wipes his eyes, trying to compose himself. Yeah. Yeah, you're probably right. Forget I said anything. #id:223
	fellow_officer: But if you change your mind... I'll be here. [color=STEEL_BLUE]Alone with my questions. And my nightmares.[/color] #id:224
	leave fellow_officer
else:
	join fellow_officer [z_index="1"]
	fellow_officer: Coincidence. Murphy laughs bitterly through his tears. Sure. And Tommy just [color=CRIMSON]vanished[/color] into thin air. #id:225
	fellow_officer: Keep telling yourself that. See how long it helps you sleep. [color=STEEL_BLUE]It doesn't help me.[/color] #id:226
	leave fellow_officer

leave fellow_officer

# Transition to Sasha scene
[background arg="res://assets/narrative/checkpoint_booth_night.png" fade="2.0"]
audio music "res://assets/music/narrative/sasha_theme_main.mp3" [fade="2.0" volume="-8.0" bus="Music"]
audio "res://assets/audio/footsteps/Metal Walk 1_2.mp3" [volume="-8.0" bus="SFX"]
join sweet_potato_sasha [z_index="1"]
sweet_potato_sasha: Sasha appears at your booth as the last shift ends. You look like you've seen a ghost. #id:227
sweet_potato_sasha: Let me guess - Murphy told you about his cousin? #id:228

if {murphy_alliance} == "ally":
	sweet_potato_sasha: Sasha nods approvingly. Good. We need people who ask questions. #id:229
else:
	sweet_potato_sasha: Sasha studies your face carefully. You're scared. That's smart. But fear won't save anyone. #id:22a

sweet_potato_sasha: I've been watching you since your first day. The way you [color=YELLOW]hesitated[/color] when Russet talked about "processing." #id:22b

if {initial_response} == "questioning":
	sweet_potato_sasha: You asked what happens to rejected potatoes. That took guts. [color=CHARTREUSE]Most just salute and stamp.[/color] #id:22c

sweet_potato_sasha: Sasha leans closer. There's a pattern. Every potato we reject? Gone within 48 hours. No deportation records. No transfers. #id:22d
sweet_potato_sasha: But [color=DARK_VIOLET]Root Reserve[/color] production? [tornado radius=3 freq=2][color=CRIMSON]It goes up.[/color][/tornado] Every. Single. Time. #id:22e

set {sasha_trust_level} = "none"
- "I believe you. How can I help?" #id:22f
	set {sasha_trust_level} = "committed"
- "I need to see proof before I risk everything." #id:230
	set {sasha_trust_level} = "cautious"

if {sasha_trust_level} == "committed":
	join sweet_potato_sasha [z_index="1"]
	sweet_potato_sasha: Sasha's eyes light up. I knew I picked right. Tomorrow night, after shift. I'll show you what I've found. #id:231
	sweet_potato_sasha: Until then, act normal. [color=YELLOW]Russet is watching everyone.[/color] #id:232
	leave sweet_potato_sasha
else:
	join sweet_potato_sasha [z_index="1"]
	sweet_potato_sasha: Fair enough. Proof is coming. Just... keep your eyes open during tomorrow's shift. #id:233
	sweet_potato_sasha: Watch where the [color=CRIMSON]rejected potatoes[/color] go. Follow the trucks if you can. #id:234
	leave sweet_potato_sasha

